    h1 Actor Based Ecosystems Simulation Software

    p Let's you develop simulations of systems consisting of multiple independent actors that interact with each other using a #[a(href="https://elm-lang.org/") delightful functional programing language Elm].


    h2 Sweet demos

    ul
      li
        h3: a.demo(href="?demo=Spreading") Spreading and Breading Demo

        p The one created in the tutorial (#[a(href="https://gitlab.com/tad-lispy/ecosystem-simulation/#installation") see the README]).

        p [#[a(href="https://gitlab.com/tad-lispy/ecosystem-simulation/blob/master/src/Demos/Spreading.elm") source code]]
      
      li
        h3: a.demo(href="?demo=Binary") Binary Demo

        p [#[a(href="https://gitlab.com/tad-lispy/ecosystem-simulation/blob/master/src/Demos/Binary.elm") source code]]

        p A sily particle simulation. There are two variants of particles: #[code Uglon] and #[code Pretton]. Every particle is attracted to #[code Pretton]. Every particle is repulsed by #[code Uglon]. There is also a #[em strong force] that acts on short distnances and repulses all particles from each other (so they don't get too cosy).

      li
